          particle than positively-charged particle. Since it has a "net" negative charge, we'd write it as Cl-.
        </div>
        <div class="feedback-incorrect feedback">
          Well, if you look at the Periodic Table, you can see that Chlorine's atomic number is 17. This means that
          it has 17 protons. Since this Chlorine atom has 18 electrons, it has one more negatively-charged particle
          than positively-charged particle. Since it has a "net" negative charge, we'd write it as Cl-.
        </div>
      </form>

